The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency ( NDLEA) says in its effort to combat the use of illicit drugs in the country it has seized over 2million kilograms of drugs worth 80 billion naira within 3 months.  The Chairman/Chief Executive NDLEA, Brig Gen. Mohammed Baba Maruwa(rtd) who made this known today as he received the Inspector General of Police IGP Usman Alkali Baba on a courtesy visit in Abuja, noted that there is need for more collaboration with the Nigerian Police in intelligence gathering.  In his remarks the IGP said the Nigerian Police Force will support the agency in policing the country of unscrupulous element using drugs adding that the police force will continue to support the DGs effort maintaining law and other across the country.